cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SY

This paper is primarily focused on wireless communications and the use of machine learning techniques for jamming attacks and defense strategies. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses security and attack strategies, which could place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Finally, the paper also involves decision-making and control, which could make it relevant to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
